{%- comment -%}
  K&A Predictive Search — Section Rendering API endpoint ONLY.

  ** 2026-07-12: confirmed NOT currently reached on this shop. **
  /search/suggest.json?section_id=ka-predictive-search was verified
  directly against production to return raw JSON, never this section's
  rendered HTML, regardless of section_id's value (tested with this
  section's real id, a bogus id, and no section_id at all — always
  identical raw JSON). assets/ka-search.js was rewired the same day to
  build the equivalent .ka-p-card markup client-side from that raw
  JSON instead (see that file's header for the full verification
  trace) and no longer depends on this section rendering. This file is
  left in place, unused but harmless, as a no-op forward-compatible
  target in case Shopify's behavior on this shop ever changes — if it
  does, ka-search.js's parseSuggestResponse() already handles the
  rendered-HTML shape too, so nothing else would need to change.

  This section is never placed in any template's "order" array and has
  no presets, so it can never be added from the theme editor's section
  picker (same convention Dawn uses for its own predictive-search.liquid).
  It exists solely to be fetched by assets/ka-search.js via:

    /search/suggest.json?q=QUERY&resources[type]=product&section_id=ka-predictive-search

  Passing `section_id` is Shopify's documented Section Rendering hook for
  the predictive search endpoint — it returns this section's rendered
  HTML instead of raw JSON, using the `predictive_search` Liquid object.

  Card markup below is copied verbatim from sections/ka-collection-grid.liquid's
  .ka-p-card block (image, name, fabric, price with the same [data-price]
  contract ka-currency.js already sweeps sitewide — spec S3) minus the
  quick-add veil, which needs a real product-page context/variant picker
  a search preview shouldn't try to replicate. Styling comes from
  assets/ka-collection-grid.css (loaded sitewide via ka-nav.liquid) and
  assets/ka-search.css's .ka-search-results__grid wrapper.

  Deliberately renders ONLY the grid, no "N pieces found for '...'" meta
  line — the `predictive_search` Liquid object exposes `resources.results.*`
  but does NOT expose the query string itself (unlike the native `search`
  object's `search.terms`/`search.performed`, used on the /search results
  page instead). assets/ka-search.js already holds the exact query it sent
  and builds that meta line client-side once this fragment arrives, rather
  than this section guessing at an unsupported Liquid property.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign products = predictive_search.resources.results.products -%}
<div class="ka-search-results__grid">
  {%- for product in products -%}
    <div class="ka-p-card">
      <a href="{{ product.url }}" class="ka-p-card__image" aria-label="View {{ product.title | escape }}">
        {%- if product.featured_image -%}
          <img
            src="{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 800 }}"
            alt="{{ product.featured_image.alt | escape | default: product.title | escape }}"
            loading="lazy"
            width="800"
            height="1067"
            class="img-filter-coll-page"
          />
        {%- else -%}
          <div style="background: var(--c-smoke); width:100%; height:100%;"></div>
        {%- endif -%}
      </a>
      <div class="ka-p-card__info">
        <p class="ka-p-card__name"><a href="{{ product.url }}">{{ product.title }}</a></p>
        {%- if product.metafields.custom.fabric_description != blank -%}
          <p class="ka-p-card__fabric">{{ product.metafields.custom.fabric_description }}</p>
        {%- endif -%}
        <p class="ka-p-card__price">
          <span data-price="{{ product.price }}">{{ product.price | money_without_trailing_zeros | replace: 'Rs.', '₹' }}</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  {%- endfor -%}
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Predictive Search",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}

